Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.99,0:00:05.98,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.43,0:00:08.49,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,If I said that, would you not do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.10,0:00:12.90,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, you have \Nevery right to refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.77,0:00:17.21,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,However, if the calamity begins...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.90,0:00:21.14,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.61,0:00:22.63,Default,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.63,0:00:25.92,Default,Yukari,0000,0000,0000,,What will the teachers \Noutside of class 3 do?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.32,0:00:29.42,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,They will cooperate to the \Nbest of their ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.42,0:00:33.15,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,However, you should not \Ndiscuss this matter
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.15,0:00:34.83,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,with anyone outside the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.83,0:00:36.60,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Not even our families?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.26,0:00:39.26,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,The rules dictate that \Nwe must not speak of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.00,0:02:15.26,Default,Board,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}May 1 (Fri.)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.10,0:02:16.85,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it wasn't going \Nto happen this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.85,0:02:18.03,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,At the opening ceremony,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.03,0:02:19.74,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,we had the perfect number of desks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:24.49,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,But we were short a desk \Nonce the new student came.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.00,0:02:27.58,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,It can start a month late?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.13,0:02:29.27,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,Looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.30,0:02:31.13,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.12,0:02:35.76,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, you checked him out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.76,0:02:36.73,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.73,0:02:38.51,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.51,0:02:39.54,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.54,0:02:41.85,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,He never lived in Yomiyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.85,0:02:42.97,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,He has no siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.10,0:02:46.29,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,And his hands weren't cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.78,0:02:48.60,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.79,0:02:59.70,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.10,0:03:03.24,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,If it's such an important rule,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.24,0:03:05.80,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,why wasn't I told about it right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.29,0:03:09.79,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You had already spoken to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.27,0:03:13.17,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That made it difficult \Nfor them to broach the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.40,0:03:18.08,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there's something \Nelse I want to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.77,0:03:21.37,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is there some reason your \Ndesk is the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.37,0:03:23.26,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,in the class that's so old?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.56,0:03:26.61,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That's part of the rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.13,0:03:31.77,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it serves some purpose \Nin completing the charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.79,0:03:35.77,Default,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Who is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.16,0:03:35.77,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the words "Who is dead?" \Nscribbled on your desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.77,0:03:38.28,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Did you write that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.96,0:03:40.01,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.01,0:03:43.28,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I know that I'm not dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.79,0:03:45.75,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,so I wanted to ask, who is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.75,0:03:47.37,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.92,0:03:49.21,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.27,0:03:52.79,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,This is my friend, Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:57.84,Default,Kirika,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome. Forgive my appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.37,0:04:00.11,Default,Kirika,0000,0000,0000,,Is he a friend from class?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:02.01,Default,Kirika,0000,0000,0000,,Or the art club?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.31,0:04:06.12,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,He's also a customer at \Nthe gallery downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.12,0:04:08.44,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,He seems to enjoy it immensely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.44,0:04:09.90,Default,Kirika,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.90,0:04:11.98,Default,Kirika,0000,0000,0000,,That's an unusual interest, for a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.43,0:04:14.01,Default,Kirika,0000,0000,0000,,You like dolls?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.57,0:04:15.89,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.89,0:04:18.81,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You should probably be \Nleaving now, Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.81,0:04:20.78,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.16,0:04:24.11,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I will see him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.33,0:04:25.65,Default,Kirika,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.65,0:04:28.27,Default,Kirika,0000,0000,0000,,Feel free to come again anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.02,0:04:33.71,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you always like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.88,0:04:35.09,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.09,0:04:36.95,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,The way you talk to your mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.95,0:04:41.33,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'd almost think you two were strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.95,0:04:45.64,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,We've pretty much always \Ntreated each other that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.64,0:04:47.39,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,What's your family like?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.81,0:04:49.47,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.57,0:04:53.15,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,She died right after I was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.47,0:04:55.51,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.53,0:05:00.54,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that was normal for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.27,0:05:03.76,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just another one of her dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.76,0:05:04.89,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,That's awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.43,0:05:08.12,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You're her daughter, her flesh and blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.12,0:05:11.08,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I may be flesh and blood, but I'm not real.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.27,0:05:14.75,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then, does your mom know about class 3?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.14,0:05:17.52,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,No, and I can't tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.85,0:05:19.96,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What does she think of you \Nskipping school so often?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.96,0:05:23.42,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't really care, \Nor she just doesn't interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.02,0:05:26.16,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Except with certain things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.16,0:05:27.30,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What things?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.04,0:05:32.63,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So, now I know class 3's secret...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:37.19,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,But how can you just accept what they're \Nputting you through to complete the charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.19,0:05:38.73,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,There's no other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.28,0:05:42.27,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I just happened to be the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.93,0:05:45.32,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,If it hadn't been me,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.32,0:05:47.49,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I would've had to follow the others
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.49,0:05:50.21,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,in treating someone else like they don't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.94,0:05:55.00,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's better that I'm the one who's cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.56,0:06:04.48,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Children's Park
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.08,0:06:23.51,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Why did they decide to make \Ntwo people nonexistent?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.09,0:06:27.74,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They probably thought the \Ncharm wouldn't hold
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.74,0:06:31.75,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,if they told you to start \Nignoring me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.36,0:06:35.52,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So by making a \Nsecond person cease to exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.52,0:06:37.87,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,they could strengthen the charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.87,0:06:38.78,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.78,0:06:40.14,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It also saved them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.14,0:06:42.92,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,the trouble of explaining me to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.92,0:06:44.53,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite logical.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.75,0:06:49.18,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,But it's just a charm, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.18,0:06:50.37,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,All of this for a charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.37,0:06:52.95,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they're desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.37,0:06:56.00,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,When they consider that they might be next,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.00,0:06:57.74,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,it makes them take it seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.92,0:07:00.64,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think they're being unreasonable?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.64,0:07:01.65,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.44,0:07:05.86,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,There are no guarantees.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.27,0:07:10.02,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But if there's a chance it could \Nhelp everyone avoid the calamity,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.02,0:07:11.23,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,isn't it worth it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.34,0:07:15.74,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's sad when people die.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.58,0:07:31.72,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.40,0:07:33.55,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful on your way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.04,0:07:36.94,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,We're both close to death, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.98,0:07:39.54,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.33,0:07:49.82,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I showed you this once before, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.19,0:07:55.14,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my left eye when I was four.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.14,0:07:57.40,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It developed a nasty tumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.40,0:08:00.83,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I woke up one day, \Nand the eye was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.50,0:08:05.60,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,My mom said a regular artificial \Neye wouldn't be attractive,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.60,0:08:08.40,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,so she made a special one for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.40,0:08:10.01,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.33,0:08:13.82,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I think your eye is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.39,0:08:18.58,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They said I almost died during surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.16,0:08:22.81,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I can sort of vaguely remember \Nwhat happened then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.81,0:08:24.18,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Do you believe that's possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.18,0:08:26.52,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You mean near-death experiences?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.97,0:08:30.02,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Death is not kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.30,0:08:33.37,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's dark, black as far as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.37,0:08:35.36,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and you're all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.66,0:08:37.02,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,All alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.73,0:08:41.29,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but it's no different \Nwhen you're alive, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.71,0:08:44.11,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many \Nrelationships we seem to have,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.11,0:08:45.55,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,we're all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.91,0:08:47.52,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I am, my mother is,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:50.11,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and you are, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.17,0:08:54.43,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,So was Misaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.33,0:08:59.50,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Starting tomorrow, \Nwe're two of a kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.50,0:09:02.69,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.89,0:09:09.96,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the club, Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.44,0:09:28.18,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hel—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.44,0:09:29.71,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Man, India's scorching!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.71,0:09:31.34,Default,Phone,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Dad
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.21,0:09:31.34,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What's with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.34,0:09:33.63,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.21,0:09:36.43,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,If you're worried about my health, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.43,0:09:37.11,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.72,0:09:40.91,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Did Mom ever talk to you about \Nher memories of junior high school?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.91,0:09:43.82,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Where's this coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.23,0:09:46.60,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Mom was in class 3 in \Nthe 9th grade, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.60,0:09:48.75,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Anything come to mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.75,0:09:50.82,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.76,0:09:52.51,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Nope!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.23,0:09:55.94,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Not a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.94,0:09:59.21,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm sure she told \Nme a few things...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.21,0:10:02.49,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,So, Ritsuko was in class 3, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.89,0:10:04.99,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, how does it feel to be back after
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.99,0:10:06.77,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,a year and a half away from Yomiyama?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.84,0:10:09.46,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,A year and a half?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.46,0:10:12.84,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,This was my first time coming here \Nsince I started junior high.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.84,0:10:15.63,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? No, I'm sure that—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.63,0:10:16.79,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.98,0:10:20.56,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.56,0:10:22.76,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,My mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.29,0:10:31.04,Default,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\fad(420,0)}Who is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.05,0:10:38.02,Default,Board,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}June 8 (Mon.)\N\NPractice Exercises \NNo whispering \NNo walking around
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.48,0:10:43.52,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.52,0:10:44.79,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Sakakibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.08,0:11:05.57,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I've gotta stop that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.25,0:11:18.32,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Kirika doesn't make lunches for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:20.37,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, when she feels like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.37,0:11:24.11,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But to be honest, they're not very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.11,0:11:25.59,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Do you ever cook?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.59,0:11:27.88,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,No, never.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.29,0:11:30.39,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I can only heat up ready-made meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.39,0:11:32.17,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that normal for kids our age?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.31,0:11:35.09,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a pretty decent cook, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.09,0:11:36.02,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.45,0:11:37.66,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That's unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.55,0:11:41.88,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I was in the cooking \Nclub at my old school.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.21,0:11:45.14,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Then, will you make me \Nsomething, someday?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.65,0:11:47.48,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.40,0:11:49.73,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,By the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.73,0:11:51.66,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,weren't you drawing up here before?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.66,0:11:53.40,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Have you finished it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.83,0:11:54.90,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.18,0:11:56.86,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Did you give her wings?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.83,0:11:58.89,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.05,0:12:02.86,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you... someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.39,0:12:04.24,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.00,0:12:07.01,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is drawing your hobby?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.78,0:12:10.74,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I think I like looking at art, \Nmore than making it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.18,0:12:14.01,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I mostly just look at art books, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.01,0:12:16.01,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,We have lots of them at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.01,0:12:17.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Do you ever go to museums?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.76,0:12:20.06,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,No, there aren't many around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.06,0:12:22.80,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you should visit me in Tokyo someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.32,0:12:24.83,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,We can go to museums there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.22,0:12:26.82,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be your tour guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.52,0:12:30.55,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Sure... someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.51,0:13:27.39,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Art Club Room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.04,0:13:31.66,Default,ArtistA,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.91,0:13:33.09,Default,ArtistC,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.09,0:13:34.81,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I just felt like dropping in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.81,0:13:36.62,Default,ArtistD,0000,0000,0000,,So, you didn't quit the club?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.62,0:13:38.84,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I just needed a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.84,0:13:40.54,Default,ArtistB,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.09,0:13:43.55,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I see Mochizuki hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.89,0:13:46.05,Default,ArtistB,0000,0000,0000,,Speak of the devil!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.13,0:13:48.58,Default,ArtistC,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, Mochizuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.09,0:13:50.46,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, um, guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.46,0:13:53.17,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Could you come with me for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.17,0:13:55.37,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,There's something we've \Ngotta do right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.37,0:13:57.86,Default,ArtistA,0000,0000,0000,,We do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.28,0:14:00.84,Default,ArtistD,0000,0000,0000,,But Misaki's here to visit us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.99,0:14:02.26,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that. Just hurry, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.31,0:14:21.77,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,At least it wasn't thrown \Naway, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.95,0:14:29.68,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Which one is your mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.68,0:14:31.26,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,This one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.96,0:14:36.14,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Ritsuko, huh? I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.14,0:14:40.40,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, is their homeroom teacher...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.04,0:14:43.81,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,He sure looked different back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.81,0:14:45.90,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,The person you mentioned before...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.10,0:14:48.75,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I was talking about Chibiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.67,0:14:51.97,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, two of you here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.86,0:14:55.82,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,There are two nonexistent people now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.82,0:14:57.41,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,So I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.41,0:15:00.63,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand the \Nsituation now, Sakakibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.63,0:15:01.75,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Mostly,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.75,0:15:05.33,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,though I still find it hard to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.33,0:15:06.67,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,That's understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.07,0:15:09.82,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,But it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.16,0:15:13.53,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,This phenomenon is truly \Nhappening in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.53,0:15:14.92,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,In this school.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.42,0:15:20.52,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You were class 3's homeroom teacher \N26 years ago, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.52,0:15:22.23,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,And that's how you knew my mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.23,0:15:23.15,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,You got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:27.94,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, is it okay for \Nyou to not ignore us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.14,0:15:30.93,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I have no connections to \Nyour class at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.93,0:15:35.37,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in a safe position, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.37,0:15:37.54,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then, who's in danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.60,0:15:39.39,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Student
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.81,0:15:39.49,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,The students of class 3
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.39,0:15:40.52,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Father | Mother\NStudent
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.49,0:15:41.62,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,and their families, within \Ntwo degrees of separation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.52,0:15:41.69,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Grandfather | Grandmother | Grandfather | Grandmother\NFather | Mother\NStudent
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.69,0:15:42.81,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Grandfather | Grandmother | Grandfather | Grandmother\NFather | Mother\NStudent\NBrothers | Sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.22,0:15:44.04,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,And they must live in Yomiyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.81,0:15:44.02,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Grandfather | Grandmother | Grandfather | Grandmother\NFather | Mother\NStudent\NBrothers | Sisters \NWithin Yomiyama
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.20,0:15:47.89,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Two degrees would mean parents, \Ngrandparents, and siblings?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.41,0:15:50.41,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,If they have to be living in Yomiyama,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.41,0:15:52.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,does that mean anyone who \Nleaves town would be safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.76,0:15:53.71,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.15,0:15:57.51,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it like a cell \Nphone going out of range.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.94,0:16:00.62,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, why do you stay here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.94,0:16:04.62,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I never meant to harm anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.62,0:16:05.82,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Never...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.31,0:16:10.43,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,It seems silly to think that way now,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.49,0:16:14.19,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,but that ended up being the trigger,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.19,0:16:16.37,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,which opened the door to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.80,0:16:20.03,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I was responsible for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.80,0:16:23.49,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I remain at this school,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.49,0:16:25.67,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,but as a librarian, not a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.13,0:16:28.80,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Half of that was just me running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.02,0:16:30.22,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Running away?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.22,0:16:32.06,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Half of me was crushed by guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.55,0:16:35.31,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,But the other half was ruled by fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.31,0:16:37.87,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Fear that I might die as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.87,0:16:39.43,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,So I ran away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.43,0:16:41.54,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Have teachers died, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.93,0:16:44.13,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Only homeroom and assistant \Nhomeroom teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.60,0:16:49.18,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, was the Misaki of 26 \Nyears ago a boy or a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.18,0:16:49.94,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,A boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.64,0:16:53.56,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,His surname was Yomiyama, \Nlike this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.56,0:16:55.76,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,His full name was Misaki Yomiyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.50,0:16:59.27,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,One night in May, his house burned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.75,0:17:02.83,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,The whole family died, parents \Nand brother included.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.26,0:17:08.46,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see the photo \Nthe dead Misaki appeared in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.46,0:17:09.48,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Sure did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.48,0:17:11.14,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.14,0:17:12.24,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.24,0:17:14.41,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you the truth, it terrified me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.41,0:17:17.75,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,And when they say the school \Nrecords somehow get altered...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.75,0:17:19.08,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.34,0:17:23.75,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,This holds copies of all class rosters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.75,0:17:27.48,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,26 years' worth, from 1972 \Nto the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:29.00,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,The people with a red "X" by their name
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:29.63,Default,Book,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Class Rosters
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.00,0:17:30.98,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,are the ones who died that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.63,0:17:33.85,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the roster from two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.85,0:17:35.49,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,See the name written at the bottom?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.49,0:17:41.51,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Deceased: Mami Asakura
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.86,0:17:37.07,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.07,0:17:39.38,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,She was the dead person that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.38,0:17:44.25,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So, seven people died in 1996?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.70,0:17:46.03,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,That's not many, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.49,0:17:49.21,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,It's because the plan to make \None person nonexistent worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.98,0:17:53.46,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,After they implemented it, \Nnobody else died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.79,0:17:56.65,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,However, shortly after the \Nsecond term began,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.65,0:17:59.79,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,the student they chose to not exist \Nended up renouncing the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.79,0:18:01.60,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Breaking under the \Npressure and isolation,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.60,0:18:05.97,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,he demanded that he existed, \Nand that everyone treat him accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.97,0:18:08.06,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,And so it began...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.27,0:18:13.02,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased in 1996 was \Nnamed Mami Asakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.56,0:18:16.90,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,But she was originally a student \Nin the 1993 class.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.90,0:18:21.63,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,However, between April and June of 1996,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.63,0:18:22.91,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,that was not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.91,0:18:24.12,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.58,0:18:25.54,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.54,0:18:29.42,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, her name was \Non the 1996 roster.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.79,0:18:33.81,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,But it was not on the roster for 1993.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.81,0:18:35.11,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,It had disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.11,0:18:36.67,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Both the name and the "X"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.16,0:18:40.72,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, when the \Nphenomenon is active,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.72,0:18:43.06,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,checking records is pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.06,0:18:46.66,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,And people's memories change too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.66,0:18:47.39,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.98,0:18:49.83,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Then, at the end of the year,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.83,0:18:52.23,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,when the deceased \Ndisappears after graduation,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.42,0:18:55.40,Default,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\fad(3000,0)}Mami Asakura
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.23,0:18:55.04,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,the records revert \Nto their original state,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.04,0:18:57.51,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,ultimately revealing the extra student.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.51,0:19:01.91,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, all memories of her \Nas the deceased are lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.91,0:19:03.67,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,All is forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.67,0:19:06.28,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,The records and memories \Njust go back to normal?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.58,0:19:08.75,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot comprehend the logic behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.11,0:19:11.19,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I've essentially given up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.63,0:19:13.49,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,There is only one countermeasure that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.49,0:19:15.89,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,seems effective against this phenomenon:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.89,0:19:19.54,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,denying the existence of \Nsomeone in the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.00,0:19:21.84,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What's the success rate?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.73,0:19:24.12,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,About 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.56,0:19:27.49,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Some years it works, others it fails.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.49,0:19:29.98,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Some years it's clear \Nwhy the measure failed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.98,0:19:31.69,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,others it's unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.14,0:19:34.35,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,That's terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.69,0:19:38.69,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.69,0:19:41.35,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,There is no malice to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.35,0:19:44.95,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,It occurs naturally, like \Na typhoon or earthquake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.95,0:19:48.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then, will having two nonexistent \Nstudents be more effective?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.76,0:19:49.91,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.91,0:19:54.05,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,There are almost no instances of \Nthe calamity stopping midyear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.44,0:19:55.42,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.76,0:19:59.69,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Mikami was class 3's \Nhomeroom teacher in 1996?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.61,0:20:02.18,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.48,0:20:06.14,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,She has been through a great deal already.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.05,0:20:10.04,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,To make her the assistant \Nhomeroom teacher again...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.15,0:20:14.79,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be all for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.79,0:20:16.24,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Just one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.24,0:20:20.78,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Was 1983, 15 years ago, \Na year when it happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.78,0:20:22.33,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,1983?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.11,0:20:25.03,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.89,0:20:28.81,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.81,0:20:32.11,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. That was Reiko's year.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.11,0:20:34.92,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Ritsuko was in Yomiyama then?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.36,0:20:36.28,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.74,0:20:39.88,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,She came here to have me, \Nand stay with her family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.83,0:20:43.23,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,So she died in this town...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.08,0:20:45.01,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.52,0:20:50.35,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Kouichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.76,0:20:51.85,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.12,0:20:54.43,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,There was nothing I could do...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.43,0:20:57.56,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,When my mom died, 15 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.99,0:21:00.19,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,was that part of the class 3 calamity?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.55,0:21:01.76,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.23,0:21:05.71,Default,Ryouhei,0000,0000,0000,,My poor Ritsuko...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.13,0:21:10.87,Default,Ryouhei,0000,0000,0000,,My poor Ritsuko... My poor Reiko, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.87,0:21:13.47,Default,Tamie,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.47,0:21:15.04,Default,Tamie,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call it a night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.50,0:21:19.09,Default,Bird,0000,0000,0000,,Cheer! Cheer up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.99,0:21:22.85,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,I honestly don't know what \Nhappened to Ritsuko,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.58,0:21:28.10,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,but I think the calamity \Nwas stopped that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.10,0:21:29.56,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,It stopped midyear?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.56,0:21:32.08,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Why? How was it stopped?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.08,0:21:33.27,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Reiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.59,0:21:34.97,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,I can't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.97,0:21:38.48,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Reiko, please, try to \Nremember something! Anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.48,0:21:40.45,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I think something may
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.45,0:21:42.03,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,have happened during summer break...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.47,0:21:43.98,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Summer break?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.98,0:21:45.67,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,I can't remember what, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.15,0:21:48.03,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Kouichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.03,0:21:50.03,Default,Board,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}July 13 (Mon.)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.02,0:22:11.18,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, class.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.55,0:22:16.23,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Today, I must apologize to you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.23,0:22:19.65,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,I have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.23,0:22:22.28,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,I have done my utmost so that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.28,0:22:24.88,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,you could all graduate in \Ngood health next spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.88,0:22:29.45,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,I did everything I could \Nto make that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.98,0:22:32.99,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,But everything that occurs henceforth \Nis for you all to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.65,0:22:36.11,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Once it has begun,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.11,0:22:41.87,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,I do not know if any amount \Nof struggling will do any good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.87,0:22:43.12,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.12,0:22:44.66,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,You can't expect me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.66,0:22:48.47,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,But I believe it is futile to \Nspeak of such things now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.92,0:24:40.29,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Sphere joint.
